# ARXOS component registry  —  name  git-url  branch  [type]
#
# This file is the single source of truth for what ships + updates on ARXOS.
# `arx update` fetches THIS file from the canonical source first, then clones/pulls
# every entry and runs its install.sh. So adding a line here pushes that component
# (a new tool, a kernel, a core update) to every ARXOS install on its next update,
# and the Control Center / arxos-news detect it automatically.
#
# type:  tool (default)  ·  core (arx/arxctl/arxupd)  ·  kernel (linux-arxos)
arx              https://github.com/thearxos/arx               main  core
arxctl           https://github.com/thearxos/arxctl            main  core
arxupd           https://github.com/thearxos/arxupd            main  core
arxos-vm-resize  https://github.com/thearxos/arxos-vm-resize   main  tool
wallpimp         https://github.com/thearxos/wallpimp          main  tool
anonkit        https://github.com/thearxos/anonkit         main  tool
cpu-governor     https://github.com/thearxos/cpu-governor      main  tool
droidB           https://github.com/thearxos/droidB            main  tool
arxguard         https://github.com/thearxos/arxguard          main  tool
